caption: Too expensive.i  feel like throwing up after having their tofu fish fried.it was $15 & they were out of chips & doubled our coleslaw but who eats bowl full of coleslaw.We orderes buffalo califlower & you only tasted buffalo sauce ! Not coming back 🤮
I hope you come back soon. I miss the deliciousness.
Average food, terrible drinks.

OMG!! I LOVE THIS AMAZING PLACE!!!!!!!!!! A tiki vegetarian dreamland!! I had reservations about trying a mock seafood dish because I don’t eat seafood and the smell is overpowering to me. But I went all in for this experience, and ordered the tofu fish and chips. WOW!!! I LOVED IT!!! The tofu was crispy and the sauce was perfect. They even had lemon and vinegar to go with. So so so delicious!!!! We also ordered the nachos. All of it was too much food! The crema on the nachos was really good. The decor in here is on another level. I truly enjoy tiki decorated places and this took it to a new standard. The bathrooms are so cool!! Sharks sticking out on the walls and shark movies playing on loop! So funny! You are doing yourself a disservice, if you don’t dine here. This is one of my all time favorite restaurants!!!
Everything is good!

Love the idea of vegan food, although not vegan myself. The place is cool and inviting with a hybrid of self service and service team. The food was good, but not outstanding. The poke bowl meal with golden beats was generous serving size.
It was good everyone liked their order but my wrap tasted better the next day when it was cold
Was good but my food was drowning in dressing. Way too heavy.

Had been craving fish and chips for a while and I was so glad I ordered them here! Delicious breaded tofu with amazing flavors in the fries, sauces and the tofu itself. We tried the Thai tea which was delicious but a little bit pricey. Side note:I would recommend they make it a no-tip place because anyway you have to get everything yourself. We had some difficulty with getting water (empty barrels) and even prepared our food leftovers to go so I felt like tipping them was unnecessary. I'd prefer that the staff are paid fair wages.

Would definitely recommend! Some of the best vegan food I've ever eaten. A little bit pricey & wifi didn't work very well (not usually a huge deal, but we were visiting from Canada and needed google maps to work) but overall a great place to eat. I would visit again if ever in Chicago.

Wow. Really cool restaurant to visit.  The ambiance is a feel of a beach. All items on the menu are vegetarian.  We ordered the poke bowl, the amaze balls, and buffalo sauce cauliflower.  They have amazing mocktails and cocktails.  We really  liked the coconut chill.  Will be going back to try more food.
Kind of expensive but delicious!
Delicious vegan food. I've taken friends and family here and they loved it. Go you won't be disappointed.
Good vegan food
I love this place!!! The service is phenomenal; always super friendly. I am not a vegan but still enjoy everything I've gotten here.
Decent food, but if you get fries you should know that they fill the bottom of the cup with cabbage
Great place

Love love No Bones Beach Club and definitely recommend it. The service is fast and friendly. You will be seated once you place your order. No matter what you get, you can’t go wrong. My favorites are the cauliflower buffalo wings, the mushroom po boy and the fries.

Really liked the interior and if you like the sea you will too. The food was a little too salty and the portions were a little bigger than I expected, but still a good place to try something new and different 👍
Tasty food, quick service, and a chill environment
Second time here and food disappointed us. There was no flavor in mushroom po boy and tropical French toast was not tasty.

Absolutely bowled over! Can’t believe we didn’t know about this place. Food is amazing and so is their staff! Very accommodating. We have a toddler that we brought (they have no phone number to call to ask questions before we came in), and there was no high chair but we had a wonderful time anyway! You guys need to open more branches! And please get a high chair 😉 love you all so much and promise that we will be back numerous times and bring others here as well! Thank you for the hospitality and delicious fresh food!
Amazing food!
Truly enjoyed our meal!
rather pricey but oh so delicious 😋 except for the tea drinks
Everything I had was delicious
Super fun venue. The menu was fun and different from most. The "bacon" was awesome.

Visited on Friday after having been here once before. Couldn't believe the amount of food we received for the price. While its always appreciative to find more vegan restaurants around, this was a let down. Two entrees with two cocktails (during happy hour) was $50.

My mom and I came for brunch on a Sunday and it was worth the trek. You enter and immediately feel like you're in a tropical oasis (even in the middle of a Chicago winter, quite an accomplishment). Grab a menu and determine what you'd like (or already have items chosen from your search on the interwebs), the staff is really great with helping select items from their menu that suit your preferences. I brought mom because she loves a Bloody Mary and theirs are listed as some of the best you can get in Chicago (not surprisingly as they're Vegan, they would have the market cornered on everyone's favorite veggie cocktail too). We ordered a half and half of the buffalo and sesame ginger cauliflower wings...so good we forgot to take a photo prior to clearing the plate. Mom ordered the chili relleno and I ordered the breakfast hash/bowl both were full of fresh whole produce and spices, but so flavorful that my omnivore mama said she could go vegan if she could eat like this all the time! It was so good, she even complimented the chef and staff on our way out. So, we know she'll definitely find her way back before I come to visit again; we loved it, something for everyone's taste buds truly.

Drinks are super good, but we had to wait in line for 30 minutes just to order two drinks. The wait would be more tolerable if they just let people order and then sit down (as opposed to making them stand so they can make and hand people the drinks at the register). Would have loved to come back, but don’t think I ever will be able to due to the way ordering is setup.
Great vegan food. Kinda pricey so be prepared!
Food was really good and I'm not a Vegan.
Up there as one of the best all-vegan places I've ever been to. Everything was great, and they do their french toast about as well as anyone, and it's stuffed which makes it even better.
The food was delicious, we ordered multiple items and they did not disappoint! The amazeballs in particular were amazing!

YUMMY!! This place has an excellent menu, that has a lovely selection of both healthy and guilty pleasure vegan food. We tried several dishes, and everything was exceptionally tasty, including their cocktails. this isn’t food that’s just good for being vegan, it is excellent no matter what your dietary decisions are. My omnivore dining partner was delighted.  I also have to add that for counter style service, it was excellent service. Someone from the staff checked on us a couple of times throughout our meal to make sure everything was just right.  The ambience is really nice as well. The music was quite enjoyable and added a nice feel to the place, without being too loud to enjoy your meal or have a conversation. I also love the beachy feel of the decorations. It made a cold Chicago night feel a little warmer.  10/10 will return!!

SO. MANY. OPTIONS ♡! The mac and cheese balls are true to their name - amazeballs. Everything i had to eat was super filling and delicious, and their cocktails are just as satisfying. Intimate space, but forever doused in a beach vibe (in the cutest way).*
This place never disappoints. It's a must visit every time I'm in Chicago
One of the best vegan burgers I’ve ever had!

Vegans delight with rare mock fish and beachy cuisine. This locations walk-up service unlike other No Bones, but is faster and less crowded so I don't mind. The seating is atrocious however; if you have any lower back problems or a bony butt I'd either stand or bring a pillow! Prices are also super steep, but kind of worth it at least on special occasions. I recommend the Painkiller (coconut, pineapple, and rum cocktail slash smoothie) and the Mac n cheese balls. The build-your-own lettuce wrap dish with soy curls is great, too. My partner always gets the taro Sando as a salad, and it's ENORMOUS.
Excellent vegan food and a nice vibe in the place! Really enjoyed the buffalo tempeh sando and the crab cakes (which didn't strike the same chord as genuine crab, but come close on the savory side.)
Amazing food and huge portions

Happy to have visited the Chicago location after going to Seattle's earlier this year. What a great spot.. A so happy to realize that most is gluten free! Vegans and non vegans alike should check this place out.
Wings a and salad I crave!!!

Jump from the cold winter days outside to a tropical beach :-). As usual we ordered way too much. Overall great food. The cauliflower bites were too soury but we finished them anyway. The Breakfast Chili Relleno was the best. The Flautas and the Nachos were Ok but a little bit pricey for what they offered. Ambience is great in a cold day. Will visit again for sure.
Everything we tried was delicious.  The drinks were good too. 😘

Nice casual atmosphere, but food just average.  Similar in quality, if different  style, than Native foods.  Fries were well cooked if a bit too spicy/salty.  I had the daily special "fish" Sando and it was OK.  Bread fell apart and tofu "fish" were too big and not overly flavorful.  There might be better options on the menu.  Service was quite friendly and I really wanted to like this place, but not impressed on my first visit.

Craved some vegan food, found this place, stopped in. There is not waited table service. Menus are on the wall along with surf board specials. Food was delicious, a little pricey, but hit the spot. Atmosphere is beach themed music fits the environment. Bathroom was a little weird as there's sharks all over, a TV and jaws was on. Definitely check it out, go with a friend, even if you don't eat your vegetables the food here is good.
Too expensive, but a good time.
Good food

I Love This bar !!!!!! Go to the bathroom whether you have to pee or not,  the shark room is a great white expedition, in the mermaid bathroom? If you don't love mermaids you need to leave. McKenzie's really great and I always enjoy going to her bar. 🦀🦈🧜‍♂️🧜‍♀️ This bar reminds me of home 🤗💗 this is Florida for me in Chicago🌞
Love the place and atmosphere!
Absolutely amazing food! My non vegan boyfriend even wants to come here all the time. Really fun atmosphere and great drinks! We had the nachos, crab cake sandwich, and avocado tacos!

I love this place. The food is unreal. I’m a regular at the Chicago Diner in Lakeview and think there can never be too many vegan stops. Hands down best vegan food in the city. The beach vibe lightens the environment and pumps out delicious cocktails. The portions are HUGE and well worth the wait. Give the pineapple teriyaki burg a try! Will def be back!
Great sandwiches! 😁 Only complaint is their $5 side of tofu is a raw quarter brick cut in half and dusted with spice 😞
Great service, and even better food.
This place is SOOOOO good ! Would highly recommend
The ambiance and food was amazing! I am pescatarian, but love vegan food so I try to find vegan restaurants in whatever city I am in. I definitely recommend the crab cakes and lettuce wraps.
All I can say is this place is outstanding!!!

My wife and I ate here for the first time and when we ordered our food and as we looked at the tables around us we realized that we may have ordered the wrong thing. Fortunately, what we ordered was good and we're looking forward to going back and trying other dishes.
Delicious vegan food
Great food and fast service! Eco friendly utensils and the decor was awesome. Will definitely come back often.
Unreal vegan seafood! Amazing drinks.

Came here with a good friend for brunch. It's not your typical restraunt because you order and pay for your food as soon as you walk in. I ordered the crab cake & fried avocado benedict with a coconut milk mojito. The benedict was super loaded, I didn't need to order anything else after that.  I went a second time with another friend during happy hour. I decided to try the vegan fish & chips (not pictured). They were SOOO good. I almost ordered another plate. My friend and I also shared some fried eggplant that was super filling. You might need to order extra sauce with it though.

Obsessed with this place! I love the Amazeballs, the Buffalo Tempeh Sando and the Pina Colada! I’ve brought friends of varying dietary needs and all have raved about NB too! I love coming back to the beach theme and really appreciate that they give back to charity! Hope they work with ALIVE rescue soon! Let’s make it happen No Bones!

6 years vegan, my Husband and I went for a mid-day date and our first time ever eating here. We tried the non alcoholic Piña Colada, a Bloody Mary, the Chili Relleno, Benedict, Buffalo Cauliflower, & Chowder. Drinks: great! Chowder: Not too bad for a vegan clam chowder. It had good flavor, but wasn't 100% a great vegan rendition. Benedict: very underseasoned. Not good. We barely ate half of it. Buffalo Cauliflower: DELICIOUS. I would go back for this for sure! Chili Relleno: my first dish wasn't cooked properly (raw flower under the fried pepper). They remade my plate, and with a little less vegan cheese, I'd say this is definitely one of my favorite vegan eats in Chicago. The service was great. And the decor is pretty snazzy.  There are some hit and misses, but I'd say the apps and service are on point!
I absolutely loved everything we ordered. The staff was really friendly and everything had so much flavor!

The crab cakes were really good, so were the drinks and fries. I also enjoyed the eggplant Spears.  The fried avocado tacos were bland, not the best. Service was excellent. I would definitely go back and try other items on the menu.
Had an amazing first experience here!
The food here is absolutely incredible. I groaned eating the tempeh sandwich as my eyes rolled back in my head. It’s that good. Def be sure to eat here!

Much like Native Foods Cafe in Wicker Park or the Chicago Diner in Logan's Square, this is a new vegan restaurant just east of the Milwaukee/North/Damen intersection.  You might be programmed to think vegan food might be boring or for sissies--- but this food is anything but boring.  I had the Buffalo "Chicken" Sandwich (not real chicken), and it blew away over 90% of real chicken sandwiches out there-- not to mention it's way healthier for you, there's no chicken raised in a tiny cage, and you're lowering CO2 emissions and land pollution by making this choice.  If you are curious about trying vegan food, check out this place for sure.  My sandwich was absolutely awesome-- it was filling (the equivalent of two sandwiches at a fast food place) and full of flavor.  Very fresh tasting and good quality, and the fries with it were great.  Price was the same as a regular chicken sandwich.  They have sandwiches, salads,  appetizers, and the cocktails were tropical type and looked impressive.  Great beach type decor on the walls and ceiling.  Tables/chairs nice and plenty of space.  Good mix of healthy vegan bowls/salads and sandwiches that imitate common American staples like Fish and Chips and Burgers.  This restaurant is based in Seattle/Portland and the Chicago location is new.

If I ever go back to Chicago, it'll be strictly to come back to this place (and the Chicago Diner). This place was amazing. The mac and cheese balls were SO good that I completely forgot they were vegan (that never happens). They also have amazing wings that I tried at the Chicago Vegandale Festival. Really great food.

Such a great spot! Everything is plant based so order away! Awesome staff very helpful and friendly. I love ordering everything i can on my first visits to new places. Definitely need to order the Amaze Balls and don’t forget to dip in their “ranch”. So delicious!
Nice, laid back with delicious drinks and food

My best friend wouldn't shut up about the food so I had to check it out for myself. Everything was so flavorful and so amazing. The El burrito is my go to every weekend now. Everyone is super nice and friendly!

i’m sorry, the people were very nice but the food was DISGUSTING. too many flavor clashes, especially with the nachos and fried mac n cheese. plus, the cashier cannot mix alcoholic drinks for her life. I ended up spending almost $60 and consuming none of it. yuck.
The food portions are big! So you're getting your money's worth here. The fishnchips & buffao cauliflower wings were very tasty!

We came here on a Sunday for brunch after pride weekend. I was hungover and starving, so it wouldn't have taken much to impress me. We ordered quite a bit off the menu. We started off strong with the nachos, very good with an authentic flare. The other standout was the french toast. It was delicious!  The other four things we ordered were almost not worth eating. We were super underwhelmed by the chowder. The breakfast bowl was a soupy salty mess and the tempeh was almost inedible. We also ordered the Tai Iced Tea and it tasted like cardboard flavored water. We walked around the area looking for a dessert, but came back to try the milkshake, but I requested it to be just a plain vanilla shake, and got a glass of ice, some kind of milk, and mint for $10. To be safe we also ordered a piece of the cake which of course was stale. So $20 gone down the drain. I really wanted to like this place, that's why we ordered so many different things, but we will not be returning.

Had the fish and chips. The fries were super soggy and everything was served in a giant oddly shaped bowl that made this meal difficult to eat. Thai iced tea was nothing to write home about either. Service was good tho.
Creative, tasty, and filling vegan dishes with many veggies, sauces, and delicious beverages.
The food was really good.
Solid vegan fare. Will definitely return.
As a non-vegan I feel weird saying this, but I may have found a new favorite restaurant in the neighborhood....
Very hearty, creative veggie food!
So so so so DELICIOUS!!!! I reccomend the AmazeBalls, the buffalo cauliflower and the mini nachos!!!! So good!!!!
This place was fun. Definitely has character, small. The theme is hit strong. But the food and drinks were excellent.  Fun.
Absolutely phenomenal food and a very fun atmosphere. Everything was packed with flavor and texture - filling and cruelty free! I would absolutely recommend this place!
Best vegan places in Chicago

This place was so good! You order your food at the bar and have a seat and the bring it to you when it's ready. I had the buffalo sandwich, which was satisfying and tasted very good. I read on their website that they donate money to animal welfare places, so I have even more of a reason to come back. Food and service was excellent!

I expected a sit down place, so I was kind of confused when I came in and found I had to wait in line with the menu, order from the bartender, then find a table. I did everything right, but I noticed other guests would try to sit down before ordering and the door man would, kind of rudely, tell people they need to order before sitting down. It was weird. Would be 5 stars if there were servers and a host instead. I went with my boyfriend who said he would've given No Bones 1 star.  The chowder was bad, but pineapple soy curls and amazeballs were awesome, and their Frozen pina colada was so ridiculously good!
They have those f$#@ing flip over ipad cash registers that force you to give them a tip for ordering something. But i have to admit, the people were nice and the food great
Great food! Friendly staff! Cool spot for vegan and vegetarian folks out there as well as anyone else who's interested in having a different kind of meal!

Loved the vibe of this place to start with. It feels like a tropical getaway when you step in. Love the little details of island vibes going on in the place. And for a vegan restaurant, they have the most creative and fun menu I've seen so far. I would recommend Amazeballs for appetizers. Love the crunch and the layers of flavors in it. Also for the entree, I would recommend the Poke bowl. Serving is huge so 2 people can share it. Also the northwest nachos is good. The chips are the bomb. For drinks, the Thai Iced Tea is so good and also sugarfree. And if you wanna try something new to drink, try out their Shark Shots. It's cute and it will surprise you.

Food and drinks superb. When you think poke, you don't think vegan, but you should because it's delicious!! Order at counter before sitting down. About five large & 10 small tables, so not a huge place, but run well with people to help seat you.

Easily some of the most fresh and interesting vegan food I've had in a long time. I've never had a hunk of tempeh like the one on the Buffalo sandwich, and the sesame ginger cauliflower wings were fried perfectly. Overall great food in a friendly, light-hearted atmosphere, and a highly recommended visit for vegan food tourists like us who can get tired of the same old routine.
Great food, great  sized portion for the price and excellent customer service!

This is a jewel of a place. When you first walk in, you would not expect the experience to be as great as it can be. When you enter, there is a short line where you order your food and drinks at a counter. Then you sit and they serve you.. So, at first, my expectations were not high. I was very wrong. It was great.  The food is all vegan. If you have not had vegan food before, in most cases you won't be able to tell the difference. Since we went for appetizers and drinks, we had only a few items. They were all delicious.  The experience ordering from the counter - we were greeted and they explained how their system worked. The person who took our order was also the bartender. The drinks were prepared while we ordered.  We only had their Eggplant Sticks, which were reminiscent of Mozzarella sticks and their wings (cauliflower, half with buffalo sauce and half with a sesame sauce). As for drinks, we had a variety. My son and I each had Mai Tais - they were different than what I expected in a pleasant way. They add bitters, normally not a part of a Mai Tai. We also had a Pina Colada at the table, and a few other drinks I don't recall. The presentation is outstanding (see the pictures I posted).  My belief is this - the space is fairly small with perhaps 20 tables. I think that once discovered, they will rapidly outgrow this location and either have to knock out a wall, find a larger space, or open another location.  Cheers to the No Bones Beach Club. We'll definitely be back.
Surprisingly delicious. Very knowledgeable staff to explain our meal . Wide variety of offerings served fresh!
Omg so freaking good. Most of the items are gluten free by default. They also serve alchohol. Which is a plus in an all vegan restaurant. Service was fast as well and friendly.
I wanted to love this place but the quality of the food doesn't match the steep prices for a counter serve concept

I’m in love with this place. 100% vegan!!! Even if you’re not vegan, the drinks and food here will totally satisfy! Favorite drinks include: coconut mojito, the drake drink. Fav brunch items: the French toast!!! and the nachos. Fav lunch/dinner: buffalo cauliflower, eggplant spears, Mac and cheese amazeballs, the Bahn mi sandwich, the avocado tacos, and the jackfruit flautas.

I had high hopes for this place. Menu looked great but food was truly inedible. Avocado tacos lacked any spice or flavor. Tried a few bites of friends dishes as well - everything tasted greasy and fried. If you're looking for a vegan version of fried lackluster barfood...sadly, this is it. All the hot sauce in the world couldn't save these dishes! Don't waste your $$$ for overpriced Instagram hype.

This is a great vegan restaurant especially for non-vegans! The service was excellent. It was crowded but they were very good at finding a table for each group. We had the sesame ginger cauliflower ...it was amazing!
Not even vegan and this is a go to place because the food is so good. I definitely recommend the buffalo wings and jack fruit flautas 👌
The nachos are great!

Loved this place. A little crowded and pretty loud, and totally worth it. The food was incredible, fresh, and outright delicious! Mostly Vegan menu, with several yummy options. Everything is clearly marked for contents and allergies. I am gluten free with dairy allergies, and had lots of choices. A friend and I split a few appetizers and couldn't even finish it was so much food! And the drinks were incredible to top it off.
Sandwiches were REALLY good! I wish they had more coat racks/hangers. I got the carrot colada and it is amazing.
Food and drinks very flavorful and interesting!

Flavorful food, fun atmosphere, and very friendly service. The highly coveted 5 stars are definitely well deserved. You will enjoy food that's very well prepared and if you're not vegan, you won't miss (or care) the lack of animal protein. The food has such a rich and lively taste, you won't realize it's entirely plant-based and it's soooooo good. Mostly GF options and not everything is fried, but the buffalo cauliflower wings and the mac and chz balls (both GF) are just incredible!
Awesome food, loved the mojitos and huevos
Great Mac and cheese poppers! #1
Great brunch/weekend menu, love the addition to any vegan sauce you can imagine.
Amazing vegan place. Excellent tiki atmosphere. Best vegan since Karen's on Green. Loved the vegan crab cakes. Large portion sizes. Great music 👌

Yummy glad that there are soy free options. The carrot colada is good. Very good service the only negative is it's a small space but they make it work with what they have. The brunch is very good also. You will not be disappointed!

The food is delicious and the drinks are amazing! Vegan or not, I highly suggest you check this place out! No Bones Beach Club chooses a new charity to donate to each month, with your purchase you are helping out a great cause! The atmosphere is so cool! It really makes you feel like you are on vacation. I’m looking forward to my next visit 🌺

I've been a vegan for a long time.  No Bones Beach Club is the best I've ever eaten and Chicago has a great selection of vegan restaurants.  I have food allergies and I'm have celiacs disease and most of the dishes are gluten free.  The most difficulty Ive had was finding that perfect balance of vegan an allergy friendly foods.  Not only does No Bones Beach Clubdo it perfectly, but the tectures and flavor combinations are so good we mostly ate in silence and moaned the whole time even in the car ride home.  As someone who likes to do gourmet vegan at home, they now have a fan and I plan on telling all my clients and friends about No Bones Beach Club.  Finally I can have dessert when I go out to dinner.  I was planning on doing anything for my birthday but my friends and I will be celebrating tbere.  I truly can't say enough about this place!

11/10 would eat here again! The vibe is really fun and the counter service makes it easy to order ALL THE THINGS (which you will do because they all look good). Portion sizes are plentiful so you won’t leave hungry. All your carnivore friends will say, “wait, this is vegan?” There are also great gluten free options—including the desserts, which is very important—and plenty of “sharable” apps if you’re rolling with a crew. The jackfruit flautas are amazing, as are the cauliflower wings. Pro tip: if you ask nicely, they will give you a half-half split of the wings so you don’t have to choose between two awesome flavors. EAT HERE AND BE HAPPY.

As a meat lover, I was pretty wary of heading to 'No Bones Beach Club' when my friend suggested it... But. I absolutely loved their food! We had the eggplant spears (so perfectly fried that it has a near-cheese texture), the crab cakes (oh-so-delicious!), and the avocado tacos (which were a wee bit disappointing). I'd definitely suggest giving this place (and those eggplant spears) a try!
I absolutely LOVE this place. Everything I've tried is fenomenal! :D

A fun, tropical adventure! This "beach-front" restaurant is an intimate place, with limited seating; but it makes up for it in the perfect tropical ambience, complete with relaxing seating and lighting. The food is all vegan, and all delicious. But I'd like to highlight the Jackfruit Flautas (flavorful taste) and Old Bay Fries (perfectly seasoned). My favorite drink would be the Piña Colada, as you hardly tasted the alcohol - until you get to the bottom of the glass, though some may prefer it that way. Either way, I'm in love! It gets busy during the after work crowd, so I'd suggest visiting during the off hours, especially since it is a little wait to get food.
Wowowowowow. The best vegan I've had in Chicago. And I've tried them all. The bartender who took my order was so friendly and fun! I got the stuffed pablano pepper and I'm just blown away, delicious!

Things were tasty, especially the eggplant fries and buffalo cauliflower. Only thing is I felt a lot of the menu is fried (aka crispy) and dishes taste pretty similar. I'd skip the carrot pina colada. Verrry sweet.

(Translated by Google) I went to celebrate my birthday there with my family and everything we tried was super tasty!  (Original) Fui a celebrar mi cumpleaños allá con mi familia y todo lo que probamos fue estupendamente rico!

Everything about this place is awesome but ONE thing - the size of their space. When they get busy theres not much breathing room! This also contributes to slight claustrophobia lol, when having to stand in line right inside the small entrance with a dozen other hungry ppl waiting for a table to open up. I could do without that part, but their delicious menu & refreshing drink variety made up for it! Loved that they donate to sanctuaries & other causes also, great message they are sending, & nice vibe!
Amazing vegan food, amazing vegan drinks, amazing vegan people, amazing vegan vibes!!! If you’re looking for the best new vegan spot in Chicago, you found it!!!

The food was amazing. I recommend the sesame salad with tempeh and the buffalo cauliflower wings. I love that they are clearly committed to cutting down on single use plastic although it would be great to have larger water cups since I had to get up to refill it myself several times. I do think they could improve the management of the restaurant- it’s an odd ordering experience. I get that it’s counter serve but we ordered our cocktails and our cashier made them immediately while we waited patiently to order the rest of our food. Then the plates and box of silverware and napkins crowded our tiny table and the servers fumbled the plates they were clearing. Another concern is that the door doesn’t close fully on its own, which seems small but makes a difference in the winter in Chicago. Finally it would be nice to see some dessert options on the menu. I saw some on instagram but didn’t get the chance to order any! I would for sure come back. I know this is a brand new restaurant and I hope they can get their process down so that they can become a Wicker Park fixture because the food is truly outstanding!

Absolutely amazed by this place's food. I haven't had a vegan buffalo chicken adaptation as good as this since becoming vegan. It was surprisingly tempeh too which was another plus. Fries were amazing too. Almost wish I lived in Chicago to eat here more and explore the rest of the menu. Venue is fun and eclectic. The staff was very friendly.
Terrible look elsewhere for vegetarian options
Love this new vegan spot!!! The food was great & the drinks were even better!! Awesome ambiance, too, just wish it were a little bigger!
Food was good but a little expensive and my fiance and I both left still hungry.
Great food, lovely service, fun ambiance! Will be going back to try out more of the menu!

I'm a carnivore, so I didn't have any food, but I had a couple cocktails, and they were good.  My main problem is with the space itself.  It's on the small side, and just awkwardly configured.  Also, even when you sit at the "bar", you have to get up and order everything from a different spot.

Fantastic and unique spot to grab some vegan grub. I’ve brought many non-vegans to this place and they’ve loved it. My favorite is to hit up brunch on the weekends. I have yet to try something I didn’t like.
Excellent food! Vegan win for Chicago. Cool atmosphere. Meat eaters don't miss the meat. Also great cocktails. Can't wait to go back.
Great food, banana killer is an amazing cocktail!

The food was delicious and when we got seated food came out quickly. Went on a saturday night very busy and we had to seat ourselves after we ordered. When we had to order more drinks i had to get up and go back to bar to leave my pretty friend to guard our stuff.  Food was a bit pricey as well .We also felt like we were being rushed out.  Overall good food good atmosphere

We went at peak dinner rush on a Saturday night at around 6:30 pm. Obviously there was going to be some wait for a table, and wait we did. The staff made it more pleasant by taking drink orders in the line since most of us were standing for 20-30 minutes waiting for tables to empty. My only complaint is that even when tables had cleared, the staff moved too slowly to take orders and seat people. Nothing is more aggravating than being hungry and waiting to eat when you can see three empty tables. So, they have to get a better handle on pacing their order lines. Once we ordered and got seated, the food came out remarkably quickly and was hot and delicious. Will definitely go back, just not 6:30 pm on a Saturday night. Vegan Fish & Chip with Old Bay fries was great and filling.
Amazing food and fun atmosphere! The buffalo cauliflower was SO good! Also recommend the avocado tacos! 😋

One gets the feeling that No Bones is something special. For the casual spot that it is, the attention to the food is remarkable. It's delicious without pretense, earnestly offering fresh and simply satisfying fare. Easily earns my respect just for its commitment to reduce animal consumption, but the fact that it also executes its food with such skill puts it in another category altogether.
